in, A.-I., Liu, Z., Shields, C., Modeling El Niño and its tropical teleconnections during the last glacial-interglacial cycle (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30, p. 2198. , doi:10.1029/2003GL018553; Peltier, W.R., Solheim, L.P., The climate of the Earth at Last Glacial Maximum: Statistical equilibrium state and a mode of internal variability (2004) Quat Sci. Rev., 23, pp. 335-357; Philander, S.G., (1990) El Niño, La Niña and the Southern Oscillation, p. 293. , Academic Press; Philander, S.G., Fedorov, A., Is El Niño sporadic or cyclic? (2003) Annu. Rev. Earth Planet. Sci. Lett., 31, pp. 579-594; Rodbell, D., Seltzer, G., Anderson, D.M., Abbott, M.B., Enfield, D.B., Newman, J.H., A 15,000 year record of ENSO-driven alluviation in Southwestern Ecuador (1999) Science, 283, pp. 516-520; Stricherz, J., Legler, D., O'Brien, J., (1997) Pacific Ocean. Vol. 2, TOGA Pseudo-Stress Atlas 1985-1994, p. 158. , The Florida State University; Timmermann, A., Oberhuber, J., Bacher, A., Esch, M., Latif, M., Roeckner, E., Increased El Niño frequency in a climate model forced by future greenhouse warming (1999) Nature, 398, pp. 694-697; Timmermann, A., Jin, F.-F., Collins, M., Intensification of the annual cycle in the tropical Pacific due to greenhouse warming (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31, pp. L12208. , doi:10.1029/2004GL019442; Trenberth, K.E., Hoar, T.J., The 1990-1995 El Niño Southern Oscillation event: Longest on record (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, pp. 57-60; Tudhope, A.W., Variability in ENSO through a glacial-interglacial cycle (2001) Science, 291, pp. 1511-1517. , Coauthors; Tziperman, E., Stone, L., Cane, M.A., Jarosh, H., El Niño chaos: Overlapping of resonances between the seasonal cycle and the Pacific ocean-atmosphere oscillator (1994) Science, 264, pp. 72-74; Uppala, S.M., The ERA-40 re-analysis (2005) Quart. J. Roy. Meteor. Soc., , Coauthors, in press; van der Vaart, P.C.F., Dijkstra, H.A., Jin, F.-F., The Pacific Cold Tongue and the ENSO mode: Unified theory within the 